spec_data.Name: backintime-common
spec_data.Description:
Back In Time is a simple backup system for Linux inspired from
“flyback project” and “TimeVault”. The backup is done by taking
snapshots of a specified set of directories.

This package contains non GUI files used by frontends.
For instance, use it as a base for headless servers,
see the manpage of backintime-config for more information.
